init_text: You're Barack Obama. 4 years into your retirement, you awake to find a letter with no return address on your bedside table. It reads "I hope you've had a chance to relax Barack...but pack your bags and call the number below. It's time to start the real job." Signed simply, "JFK."

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: You throw on some clothes, and call the number.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: An old familiar voice picks up on the other line, "It's time to get to work.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: Sorry for the letter, but I didn't have a chance to talk with you before you left office.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: I need you to do exactly as I say, you'll be working with some familiar faces from the old days."

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: JFK continues, "I promise you'll find it all very interesting, but for now, be ready to fly out in the next hour

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: You pack your bags and head to the airport.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: On the plane, you're joined by Jackie O's spirit.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: "You've got a lot to learn about the spirit world, but I'll give you a quick primer.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: You can see, hear, and interact with me right now.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: You can talk to other spirits who have crossed over, but you can only see them when they want you to.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: When you leave this plane, you'll enter the spirit realm.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The rules are different over there.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: You'll be able to see and hear everyone, but they won't be able to see or hear you.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: You'll be working with a team of people from all around the world.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: "Your first job is to find a veteran who voted for Trump.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: He's been having some troubles adjusting to civilian life.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: He's a good man who has a lot to offer, but there are some demons in his past that have been haunting him.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: Get to him before those demons do."

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: You arrive in Vegas, you're met by Malcolm X.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: "You're late...I'll fill you in on the way to the casino."

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: Your whole team is here, Martin Luther King Jr., Malcolm X, JFK, MLK JR., John Lennon, and even Gandhi.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The limo pulls up to the front of the Bellagio.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: You all enter the casino and make your way to a private room on the top floor.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: Inside the room, you see a large round table with 9 chairs.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: JFK says, "Alright gentlemen, I'll get right to it.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The Trump voter you have to reach is a man named Mike.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: He was a good man, raised by two wonderful parents.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: They died in a car accident when he was 19, and that's when everything went wrong for Mike.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: He got into drugs, and started homeless.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: He joined the marines right before he turned 21, and he fought his way to Iraq.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: There, he saw his friends being blown to pieces by IEDs and suicide bombers.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The last thing he remembers is seeing his friend's brains splatter against the wall of a house in Fallujah.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: He woke up in a hotel room with his friend's blood on his hands, and no memory of what happened to him.
